---
import carousel1 from '/src/img/carousel-1.png';
import carousel2 from '/src/img/carousel-2.png';
import carousel3 from '/src/img/carousel-3.png';
import carousel4 from '/src/img/carousel-4.png';

import './TabComponent.scss';

---
  
  <div class="tabs-container">
    <div class="tabs">
      <div class="tab-content active" data-tab="1">
        <h1>AI-powered research, unlimited answers</h1>
        <p>Create the ultimate authority on your target companies. Our research tools let you build deep research libraries that go beyond basic data. </p>
        <p>Our research agents work just like a human, using context to understand the questions you’re asking and how to frame their responses. Your data is clean, useful, and immediately usable. </p>
      </div>
      <div class="tab-content" data-tab="2">
        <h1>Connected to the way you work</h1>
        <p>Easily connect your CRM, then setup rules to define how to push and pull prospect data. You’re in control of your information, with custom rules at a company and campaign level.</p>
        <p>Data not in a CRM? No problem! Import information from CSVs, or scan your past conversations to extract and enrich prospects.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tab-content" data-tab="3">
        <h1>Turbocharge your sales team’s output</h1>
        <p>Say goodbye to simple templates, and hello to individually personalised messaging. The data you gather directly drives high-quality messages. Setup your lists and research, and your sales team automatically has access to all your information when crafting messages. </p>
        <p>Use Sales Triggers to define not just what’s in a message, but when it’s sent. Meaning your team is sending the right message at the right time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tab-content" data-tab="4">
        <h1>Automate your entire GTM process</h1>
        <p>Isn’t it time computers did the difficult work? Applied Thought lets you set and forget; defining your sources, targets and then sitting back whilst our AI-platform makes you look good. </p>
        <p>Stay in control over sourcing, prospecting, and messaging with approvals. Or use agent-approval to only escalate when human intervention is needed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="content-images">
      <div class="images">
        <img src={carousel1.src} alt="Image 1" class="tab-image tab1 active" data-tab="1">
        <img src={carousel2.src} alt="Image 2" class="tab-image tab2" data-tab="2">
        <img src={carousel3.src} alt="Image 3" class="tab-image tab3" data-tab="3">
        <img src={carousel4.src} alt="Image 4" class="tab-image tab4" data-tab="4">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <script>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const tabContents = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.tab-content');
      const tabImages = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.tab-image');
  
      tabContents.forEach(content => {
        content.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const tabId = content.getAttribute('data-tab');
  
          // Remove active class from all tab contents
          tabContents.forEach(cnt => cnt.classList.remove('active'));
          content.classList.add('active');
  
          // Hide all images
          tabImages.forEach(img => img.classList.remove('active'));
  
          // Show active image
          document.querySelector<HTMLElement>(`.tab-image[data-tab="${tabId}"]`)?.classList.add('active');
        });
      });
  
      // Set the first tab content as active initially
      tabContents[0].click();
    });
  </script>
  